HEADWORD: Ombrometer
<hw>Om*brom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ rain +
<ets>-meter</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ombrom⟦eacute⟧tre</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteorol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the rain that
falls; a rain gauge.</def>⟦br⟧
